included.summary:
Abbie is an enthusiastic technology and usability evangelist. With a Master's Degree in Human-Computer Interaction and a B.A. in Psychology, experience in usability research and technical support, she approaches every challenge with curiosity, determination and empathy. 

Abbie enjoys a stimulating User Experience Research career, working with organizations who strive to make a positive social impact on the world and to empower women and minorities. 

In UX roles, Abbie leads in and collaborates on the creation, testing, analyses and refinement of unique, usable and lovely software and website User Interface (UI) designs and overall user experiences, from early ideation through post-launch patches.

"Towards delight."
included.headline: User Experience Researcher & Strategist at Excellus

included.description:
Utilized a variety of qualitative research methods to analyze the User Interface (UI)--including user testing, heuristic evaluation, cognitive walkthroughs and task analyses--of La Fuente de Los Leones (Fountain of the Lions) virtual reality software application (for the Alhambra in Granada).

This software was designed and developed by professors at the University of Granada Virtual Reality Lab. Conducted this usability research in collaboration with fellow students of the graduate Human-Computer Interaction program at SUNY Oswego during our summer research project abroad in Granada, Spain.
included.title: Cross-Cultural, Bilingual Virtual Realty Research at UGR
